slime-cheat-sheet
help-for-help				C-h ?, C-h C-h	shows various help options
slime-describe-symbol			C-c C-d d
slime-compile-and-load-file
slime-compile-defun
slime-compile-file
slime-eval-buffer			C-c e
slime-eval-defun			C-M-x		eval this top-level form
slime-eval-region
slime-eval-last-expression		C-x C-e		eval the form preceding the cursor, shows the result in status bar
slime-edit-definition			M-.		jumps to the definition of the function (macro, ...) the cursor is on
slime-pop-find-definition-stack		M-,		jumps back
slime-expand-1-inplace			C-c RET		calls macroexpand-1, shows the result in new buffer
slime-highlight-notes/slime-remove-notes
slime-inspect				C-c I		evaluates expression and inspects its result
slime-inspect-presentation-at-point	C-c C-v i	inspects result the cursor is on (in the repl)
slime-next-note/slime-previous-note	M-n/M-p		the error is written in the status bar
slime-reindent-defun			C-c M-q		reindents the top-level form
slime-repl-clear-buffer			C-c M-o
slime-switch-to-output-buffer		C-c C-z		switches to repl
slime-toggle-trace-fdefinition		C-c C-t		toggles tracing of the function whose definition the cursor is on
slime-list-callers			C-c <		lists function callers, hit space on the caller - jump to definition
slime-list-callees			C-c >
backward-sexp				C-M-b		jump one s-exp back
forward-sexp				C-M-f		jump one s-exp forward
kill-sexp				C-M-k		delete the s-exp
indent-sexp				C-M-q		indent the s-exp correctly
hyperspec-lookup
*slime-compilation* buffer (R/O) - lists errors and warnings, when I hit return, shows the code with colored underlines

debugger:
t - toggle detail
v - go to source code
a - abort
i - evaluate expression in current environment
RET - inspects current object

F3 editace F4 - define-kdb-macro
start-kbd-macro -> end-kbd-macro -> call-last-kbd-macro

zapnuti optimalizace pro debug:
(declaim (optimize (speed 0) (safety 3) (debug 3)))
